-- Global hedge fund assets hit record high in April - eVestment
-- By Simon Jessop
-- Thu May 15, 2014 05:28AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, May 15 (Reuters) - Global hedge fund assets under management hit an all-time high of $2.938 trillion in April, beating the previous peak of $2.937 trillion reached before the financial crisis, data provider eVestment said.

"Investors allocated heavily into hedge funds in April, the third consecutive month of elevated inflows," it said in a statement.